# Cloudflare static-asset response headers (copied verbatim into ./out and served
# by the Worker). Applied to every route. HSTS is already set at the edge; these
# add the defense-in-depth headers a static content site should carry. No CSP:
# Next ships inline hydration + JSON-LD scripts, so a strict policy would need
# 'unsafe-inline' and buy little — clickjacking is covered by X-Frame-Options.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
